{{Infobox language |name=Basketo |states=[[Ethiopia]] |ethnicity= |speakers={{sigfig|92600|2}} |ref=e18 |date=2007 census |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Omotic languages|Omotic]] |fam3=[[North Omotic languages|North Omotic]] |fam4=[[Ometo languages|Ometo]] |fam5=North |iso3=bst |glotto=bask1236 |glottorefname=Basketo }}
'''Basketo''' (also known as Basketto, Baskatta, Mesketo, Misketto, and Basketo-Dokka) is an [[Afro-Asiatic languages|Afro-Asiatic]] language spoken in the [[Basketo special woreda]] of the [[Southern Nations, Nationalities, and Peoples Region]], which is part of [[Ethiopia]].<ref name=e18/> The speakers refer to the language as "Masketo", while their neighbors refer to it as "Basketo." It has said to consist of two dialects, "Doko" (Dokko) and "Dollo" (Dollo). Besides their mother tongue, some also speak [[Melo language|Melo]], [[Oyda language|Oyda]], [[Galila language|Galila]], or [[Gofa language|Gofa]].<ref>Alemayehu Abebe, [http://www.sil.org/silesr/2002/SILESR2002-067.pdf "Sociolinguistic Survey Report of the Mesketo Language of Ethiopia"], SIL Electronic Survey Reports SILESR 2002-067.</ref>
