{{Expand Belarusian|Пераклады Бібліі на латышскую мову|date=December 2014}}
The [[Lutheran]] pastor [[Johann Ernst Glück]] translated the Bible into the [[Latvian language]] in 1685. 

This translation was republished many times, repeatedly re-edited. Most recently a revision was begun in 1931 and printed in 1965 by the [[United Bible Societies]], London. For this the main language editor was Professor [[Ernests Blese]]. This translation used the traditional "ch" and "ŗ" of pre-war [[Latvia]] and [[Latvian people|Latvians]] in exile. 

In 1995 [[The Latvian Bible Society]] (LBB) began work on a new Bible translation; [[Gospels and Acts]] 1999, the whole [[New Testament]] 2007. The Publishing House "Zinātne" ("Science") has issued a number of Old Testament books in some editions, but the LBB's Old Testament translation is still being prepared for publication. In 2005 the Latvian Bible Society issued the Deuterocanonical books.

