{{refimprove|date=August 2015}} '''Export of revolution''' is actions by a victorious [[revolution]]ary [[government]] of one country to promote similar revolutions in unruled areas or other countries, as a manifestation of revolutionary [[internationalism (politics)|internationalism]] of certain kind, e.g., the [[Marxist]] [[proletarian internationalism]].<ref name=halliday>"Revolution and World Politics", by [[Fred Halliday]] (1999) {{ISBN|0-8223-2464-4}}, [https://www.google.com/books?id=3jCkXQRhHMgC&pg=PA94&dq=%22export+of+revolution%22#PPA94,M1 "Internationalism in Practice: Export of Revolution" pp. 94&ndash;132]</ref>
[[Fred Halliday]]<ref name=halliday/> analyzes the traits of the export of revolution by case studies of [[French Revolution]], [[Russian Soviet Federative Socialist Republic|Soviet Russia]]/[[Soviet Union]], [[People's Republic of China]], [[Cuba]] of [[Fidel Castro]], and [[Iran]] of [[Ayatollah Khomeini]].
