'''Hamont dialect''' or '''Hamont Limburgish''' is the [[dialect|city dialect]] and variant of [[Limburgish language|Limburgish]] spoken in the [[Belgium|Belgian]] city of Hamont (a part of [[Hamont-Achel]]) alongside the [[Dutch language]] (with which it is not mutually intelligible).{{sfnp|Verhoeven|2007|p=219}} In the Achel part of Hamont-Achel, another dialect called [[Achels]] is spoken.

