{{Infobox language |name = Damana |nativename = Malayo |pronunciation = |states = [[Colombia]] |region = [[Sierra Nevada de Santa Marta]] |speakers = 1,850 |date =2007 |ref=e18 |familycolor= American |fam1= [[Chibchan languages|Chibchan]] |fam2 = Arwako–Chimila |fam3 = Arwako |iso3 = mbp |glotto=mala1522 |glottorefname=Malayo |map= wiwalanguage.png }}
'''Damana''' (also known as '''Malayo''', '''Wiwa''', '''Arosario''', '''Arsario''', '''Guamaca''', '''Guamaka''', '''Maracasero''', '''Marocasero''', '''Sancá''', '''Sanja''', '''Sanka''', '''Wamaka''')<ref name="ethnologue">{{cite web|title=Malayo|website=Ethnologue|access-date=12 April 2018|url=https://www.ethnologue.com/18/language/mbp/}}</ref> is a [[Chibchan languages|Chibchan language]] spoken by the indigenous [[Wiwa people]] on the southern and eastern slopes of [[Sierra Nevada de Santa Marta]] in northern [[Colombia]]. According to Ethnologue, it was spoken by 1,850 people in 2007;<ref name="ethnologue"/> however, according to the Colombian Ministry of Culture, there were 13,627 Wiwa people in 2010, of whom some 60% speak Damana well.<ref name="Ministerio de Cultura">{{cite web|title= Un poco más de la mitad de la población wiwa habla bien la lengua damana |trans-title=A little more than half of the Wiwa population speak Damana well|language=Spanish|date=24 February 2010|access-date=12 April 2018|website=Ministerio de Cultura, Colombia|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100327132330/http://www.mincultura.gov.co/index.php?idcategoria=34350}}</ref>
